Version with: - No Data Oriented Design - Visualisations: - J2D
Version with: - No Data Oriented Design - Visualisations: - J2D

Restructured moving system from Object to Data Oriented Design. This includes: - Adding a MovementComponent - Structure containing position and speed values - Adding a MovementUpdater - Object containing methods to update the position of an Object depending on their type - Removing every "move" method in objects - Restructuring the AbsInput and KeyboardInput1 objects - Combining AbsPlayer1.java and AbsPlayer2.java into AbsPlayer - Adding a playerId, ownId and ownColor - Changing how inputs are read - Deleting J2DPlayer1.java and J2DPlayer2.java - Creating J2DPlayer
Cleaned up the code a bit.
Added a pause function. This includes: - Pause the game loop and timers - Updated the Timer object: - Added "Pause" and "Start" methods - Add visual "PAUSED" on the screen
Added a new SpriteVisualisation, this contains: - New sprites for AbsEnemy, AbsPlayer and AbsPowerup - Added background to JFrame
Made heading more transparent and centered gamePanel in gameFrame
Added: - Bullet sprites (Green, Blue, Yellow, Red) - Sound effect (currently only for AbsPlayerBullet)
Added: - Bullet sprites (Green, Blue, Yellow, Red) - Sound effect (currently only for AbsPlayerBullet)
Added: - Sound effects and background music
